# BasicKtorServer â€” Scope of Improvements

Analysis based on a full review of all 16 source files, build configuration, and project structure.

---

## 1. đź”´ Security

| # | Issue | Where | Details |
|---|-------|-------|---------|
| 1.1 | **Hardcoded JWT secret** | [Config.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/config/Config.kt) | `JWT_SECRET = "my-auth-secret-key"` is checked into source. Should be loaded from env vars or [application.yaml](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/resources/application.yaml). |
| 1.2 | **Hardcoded seed user with weak password** | [DatabaseFactory.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/data/DatabaseFactory.kt#L21-L26) | `password123` is inserted on every boot. Remove or gate behind a dev-only flag. |
| 1.3 | **PUT/DELETE users not authenticated** | [Route.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/routes/Route.kt#L97-L114) | `PUT /{id}` and `DELETE /{id}` under `/users` have no `authenticate` wrapper â€” anyone can call them. |
| 1.4 | **No input validation** | All `call.receive<>` sites | No length/format/regex validation on `username`, `email`, `password`, `title`, `content`. Malformed or oversized inputs go straight to the DB. |
| 1.5 | **No rate limiting** | Globally | Login and register endpoints are open to brute-force and credential-stuffing. |
| 1.6 | **No CORS configuration** | [Application.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/Application.kt) | If a frontend will call these APIs, CORS needs to be configured. |

---

## 2. đźź  Architecture & Code Quality

| # | Issue | Where | Details |
|---|-------|-------|---------|
| 2.1 | **Monolithic route file (231 lines)** | [Route.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/routes/Route.kt) | All routes (pages, auth, users, notes) live in one file. Split into `AuthRoutes.kt`, `UserRoutes.kt`, `NoteRoutes.kt`. |
| 2.2 | **No service/repository layer** | Route handlers | DB queries (`transaction { ... }`) are written inline inside route handlers. Extract a `UserRepository` and `NoteRepository` (or service classes) for separation of concerns and testability. |
| 2.3 | **Repeated "get user from token" pattern** | [Route.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/routes/Route.kt#L121-L125) | The pattern of extracting `username` â†’ looking up `usrId` â†’ null-checking is duplicated in every note endpoint. Extract into a helper or middleware. |
| 2.4 | **Inconsistent model design** | `model/` package | `NoteRequest` is a mutable class with default `""` values instead of a `data class`. `ErrorResponse`, `Profile`, etc. have `@Serializable` but the project uses Gson, not `kotlinx.serialization`. |
| 2.5 | **Duplicate dependency** | [build.gradle.kts](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/build.gradle.kts#L31-L33) | `ktor-server-content-negotiation` is declared twice (lines 31 & 33). |
| 2.6 | **Redundant `Server.kt`** | [Server.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/Server.kt) | The app launches via `EngineMain` (per `build.gradle.kts`), making the `embeddedServer` main in `Server.kt` a second, unused entry point. Remove or unify. |
| 2.7 | **Unused model classes** | `RegistrationForm.kt`, `Profile.kt` | `RegistrationForm` is received on `PUT /users/{id}` but the handler is a stub. `Profile` returns a hardcoded object. Clean up or implement. |

