## 3. đźźˇ Database

| # | Issue | Where | Details |
|---|-------|-------|---------|
| 3.1 | **In-memory H2 database** | [DatabaseFactory.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/data/DatabaseFactory.kt#L14-L17) | Data is lost on every restart. Add a persistent DB option (Postgres, file-based H2) with env-based config. |
| 3.2 | **No DB migrations** | `DatabaseFactory.init()` | Only `SchemaUtils.create()` is used. For any schema evolution, a migration tool (Flyway, Liquibase) is needed. |
| 3.3 | **No unique constraint on `username`** | [Users.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/data/models/Users.kt) | Uniqueness is enforced only by application logic in the register handler, not at the DB level. A race condition can create duplicates. |
| 3.4 | **No `createdAt` / `updatedAt` timestamps** | `Users.kt`, `Notes.kt` | Standard audit columns are missing. |
| 3.5 | **No connection pooling** | `DatabaseFactory.kt` | For a production DB, add HikariCP connection pooling. |

---

## 4. đź”µ Testing

| # | Issue | Details |
|---|-------|---------|
| 4.1 | **No `src/test` directory at all** | The project has zero tests â€” no unit tests, no integration tests. |
| 4.2 | **Route handlers are untestable** | Inline DB access and no dependency injection make it impossible to unit-test business logic without a running DB. |
| 4.3 | **Test dependencies exist but unused** | `ktor-server-test-host` and `kotlin-test-junit` are in `build.gradle.kts` but never used. |

---

## 5. đźź˘ API Design & Error Handling

| # | Issue | Where | Details |
|---|-------|-------|---------|
| 5.1 | **Inconsistent error responses** | Various route handlers | Some endpoints respond with plain strings (`"Invalid credentials"`), others with `ErrorResponse`, others with `Map`. Standardize on a single error envelope. |
| 5.2 | **`UserNotFoundException` returns 200** | [Application.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/Application.kt#L56-L59) | The `StatusPages` handler for `UserNotFoundException` calls `call.respond(errorResponse)` without setting an HTTP status code â€” defaults to 200 OK. Should be 404. |
| 5.3 | **Stub endpoints** | `PUT /users/{id}`, `DELETE /users/{id}` | These handlers return success messages but perform no actual database operations. |
| 5.4 | **No pagination** | `GET /users`, `GET /notes` | These return all rows with no limit/offset. Will degrade with data growth. |
| 5.5 | **No API versioning** | All routes | Routes are unversioned (e.g., `/users` instead of `/v1/users`). Makes future breaking changes harder. |
| 5.6 | **`/login` sits under `pagesRouting`** | [Route.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/routes/Route.kt#L36-L54) | Authentication logic is grouped with static page routes. Move to a dedicated auth route file. |

---

## 6. âš™ď¸Ź Configuration & DevOps

| # | Issue | Details |
|---|-------|---------|
| 6.1 | **No environment-based configuration** | `Config.kt` has all values hardcoded. Use `application.yaml` profiles or env variables for different environments. |
| 6.2 | **No Docker support** | No `Dockerfile` or `docker-compose.yml` for containerized deployment. |
| 6.3 | **No CI/CD pipeline** | No GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, or similar workflow files. |
| 6.4 | **No request logging** | Add Ktor's `CallLogging` plugin for observability. |
| 6.5 | **Minimal `application.yaml`** | Only port and module are configured; all other config is in code. |

---

## 7. đź“¦ Build & Dependencies

| # | Issue | Details |
|---|-------|---------|
| 7.1 | **Gson instead of kotlinx.serialization** | Several models already use `@Serializable` from `kotlinx.serialization`, but the app uses Gson for content negotiation â€” a mismatch. Pick one. |
| 7.2 | **`@Serializable` annotations are unused** | Since Gson is used, the `@Serializable` annotations on `ErrorResponse`, `Profile`, etc. do nothing. |
| 7.3 | **ApiClient uses wrong password** | [ApiClient.kt](file:///Users/buddhasaikia/work/IdeaProjects/BasicKtorServer/src/main/kotlin/com/bs/basicktorserver/client/ApiClient.kt#L31) | The client sends `"123456"` but the seeded user's password is `"password123"`. This will always fail. |
| 7.4 | **Client lives in `main` source** | `ApiClient.kt` is a test/demo client but resides in the production source set. Move to a `test` or separate module. |

